          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Do SaaS companies need custom websites or are AI builders sufficient?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">AI builders are sufficient for most early-stage SaaS companies. Modern AI builders create professional landing pages that look custom-made for marketing sites, product showcases, and user acquisition. AI builders excel at: beautiful pricing tables, feature displays, testimonials, integration links, signup flows, and changelog sections. Consider custom development only when: (1) You have complex interactive product demos, (2) Need real-time data integration in frontend, (3) Have specific technical requirements, (4) Raised funding and ready for significant investment. Most successful SaaS companies start with AI builder landing pages, validate their market, then invest in custom development after product-market fit. Framer and Webflow both offer code export for smooth transition to custom development when ready.</p>
